
 1. Docker Installation & Version
docker --version → Check Docker version
docker info → Detailed system info

 2. Docker Images
docker pull <image> → Download image
docker images → List images
docker rmi <image> → Remove image
docker build -t <name> . → Build image from Dockerfile
 Example:
docker pull nginx
docker build -t myapp .


 3. Docker Containers
docker run <image> → Run container
docker run -it <image> → Interactive mode
docker run -d <image> → Run in background
docker ps → Running containers
docker ps -a → All containers
docker stop <container> → Stop container
docker start <container> → Start container
docker restart <container> → Restart container
docker rm <container> → Delete container

Example:
docker run -d nginx
docker ps

 4. Container Interaction
docker exec -it <container> bash → Access container
docker logs <container> → View logs
docker inspect <container> → Detailed info

 5. Port Mapping & Naming
docker run -p 8080:80 nginx → Map ports
docker run --name mycontainer nginx → Name container

6. Volumes (Data Persistence)
docker volume create <name> → Create volume
docker volume ls → List volumes
docker volume rm <name> → Delete volume
 Use volume:
docker run -v myvolume:/data nginx










 7. Docker Networks
docker network ls → List networks
docker network create <name> → Create network
docker network rm <name> → Delete network

Run container in network:
docker run --network mynet nginx

8. Dockerfile Commands (Basics)
FROM → Base image
RUN → Execute command
COPY → Copy files
CMD → Default command
EXPOSE → Define port

Example:
FROM ubuntu
RUN apt update
CMD ["echo", "Hello"]

 9. Cleanup Commands
docker system prune → Remove unused data
docker container prune → Remove stopped containers
docker image prune → Remove unused images

 10. Docker Compose (Basic)
docker-compose up → Start services
docker-compose down → Stop services
docker-compose ps → List services


























